  {
    "title": "Lore",
    "depth": 1,
    "paragraphs": [
      {
        "sentences": [
          {
            "text": "Legends say that an ancient race of elves reside in the Land of Dawn's Enchanted Forest.",
            "links": [
              {
                "type": "internal",
                "page": "Land of Dawn"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": "The stories often depict this cat-like race as small in stature, agile, playful, independent, and highly intelligent."
          },
          {
            "text": "However, few are aware of the longstanding alliance between the Leonin Elves and the Moon Elves."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "sentences": [
          {
            "text": "From a young age, Harith surpassed his peers in talent and wisdom."
          },
          {
            "text": "He quickly became the strongest mage among the Leonins, perhaps as strong as other in the Land of Dawn."
          },
          {
            "text": "Although, the Leonins never step foot outside of the Enchanted Forest, living a peaceful and safe life on their own."
          },
          {
            "text": "The Leonins became so complacent with their blissful existence that they no longer pursed the magic arts, a hallmark of their people."
          },
          {
            "text": "Harith became very discontent with this trend and confidently set out of the Enchanted Forest to see the outside world at the young age of 15."
          },
          {
            "text": "Harith was driven by his and passion for the magic arts, aspiring to become his people's leader in magic."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "sentences": [
          {
            "text": "Harith arrived at the Moniyan Empire, where he joined armies to fight off the invading orc tribes.",
            "links": [
              {
                "type": "internal",
                "page": "Moniyan Empire"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": "Proving himself in battle, Harith gained the recognition of Tigreal, who came to appreciate Harith 's lovely spirit and strong abilities.",
            "links": [
              {
                "type": "internal",
                "page": "Tigreal"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": "People say, Harith was given the rank of lieutenant and will soon be appointed as an Imperial Master of Magic of the Moniyan Empire."
          },
          {
            "text": "With that said, Harith has imperial authorization to use magic to control space and time to unlock the Secrets of Dawn to seal away evil and protect justice."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "sentences": [
          {
            "text": "Full of excitement and fervor, Harith also knew that once he is appointed the title of Master of Magic that he will become a target of public criticism."
          },
          {
            "text": "Committed to his dream of becoming his people's leader in magic, Harith fearlessly marched forward alone."
          },
          {
            "text": "Over time, Harith discovered that his life was consumed by his mission and by the empire."
          },
          {
            "text": "Harith slowly grew lonely and reclusive."
          },
          {
            "text": "Even when he met his fellow Leonin, Nana, he was unable to maintain a normal conversation.",
            "links": [
              {
                "type": "internal",
                "page": "Nana"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": "Despite Nana showing signs of affection towards him, he could not express his feelings, believing that the best way to protect her from criticism was for him be alone."
          },
          {
            "text": "After all, whenever the empire needed magical assistance, the Master of Magic was on the job to seal away the dangers of evil."
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "templates": [
      {
        "template": "clr"
      }
    ]
  },
